results.name: Differences of A011757 ("Primes with square indices").
comment: Does a(n) = k^2 have infinitely many solutions? E.g., 16 = 4^2; 576 = 24^2; ...
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
program: (PARI) { default(primelimit, 2*10^7); for (n=1, 1000, write("b063076.txt", n, " ", prime((n+1)^2) - prime(n^2)) ) } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Aug 17 2009
